The paper proposes a method to transform a block that outputs an optimal discrete decision into a differentiable operation, which can be used in machine learning pipelines. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of this method in structured prediction, which is a sub-field of machine learning that involves predicting structured outputs such as sequences or graphs, suggesting that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision (cs.CV), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), or Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
